# i18n Rule — All UI Text Must Be Translated

This project supports 12 languages. **Every user-visible string must come through the translation system.** Never write a raw string literal where the user can see it.

## How the system works

- **Single source of truth**: `frontend/src/contexts/LanguageContext.tsx`
  - `MESSAGES.de` — German (default/primary)
  - `MESSAGES.en` — English
  - `MESSAGES.fr` — French
  - `LANGUAGE_OVERRIDES.{es,it,pt,tr,ru,hi,ar,zh,ja}` — merge over `en`

- **In pages / components**: use `useLanguage()`
- **In widgets**: use `useWidgetLanguage()`

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
const { t } = useLanguage();
<p>{t("myNewKey", "Fallback in English")}</p>

// ❌ WRONG — hardcoded text
<p>No tasks yet</p>
<p>Noch keine Aufgaben</p>
```

## Rules to follow every time you add or edit a file

### 1. No hardcoded strings in JSX or return values
Any text the user can see — labels, placeholders, titles, tooltips, `aria-label`, empty states, error messages — must call `t("key", "English fallback")`.

### 2. Always add the key to ALL three primary languages
When you add a new key, add it to **`MESSAGES.de`**, **`MESSAGES.en`**, and **`MESSAGES.fr`** in `LanguageContext.tsx`. The other 9 languages inherit from `en` automatically.

```ts
// In MESSAGES.de:
myNewKey: "Deutsch",

// In MESSAGES.en:
myNewKey: "English",

// In MESSAGES.fr:
myNewKey: "Français",
```

### 3. Use English as the fallback, never German
```tsx
// ✅ English fallback
t("tabOverdue", "Overdue")

// ❌ German fallback — will show German when key is missing
t("tabOverdue", "Überfällig")
```

### 4. Static arrays/constants with labels must be inside the component (useMemo)
If a constant has user-visible labels (like tab lists, section headers, dropdown options), define it inside the component with `useMemo` so labels react to language changes.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — reactive to language
const tabs = useMemo(() => [
  { id: "today", label: t("tabToday", "Today") },
  { id: "overdue", label: t("tabOverdue", "Overdue") },
], [t]);

// ❌ WRONG — static, language never updates
const TABS = [
  { id: "today", label: "Heute" },
];
```

### 5. Relative time and date strings must use t()
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
t("relTimeJustNow", "Just now")
t("relTimeMins", "{n} min ago").replace("{n}", String(mins))

// ❌ WRONG
`vor ${mins} Min.`
"Gerade eben"
```

### 6. Key naming convention
Use camelCase, grouped by feature prefix:
- `tab*` — filter tabs (tabToday, tabOverdue, tabAll…)
- `tasks*` — task widget strings
- `notif*` — notification panel
- `settings*` — settings page
- `common*` — shared actions (commonSave, commonCancel, commonEdit…)
- `relTime*` — relative timestamps
- `dueDate*` — due date display labels

### 7. When editing TasksWidget or adding new widgets
- Task preset labels → add `taskPreset{Name}` keys to MESSAGES
- Priority labels → use existing `tasksHigh`, `tasksMedium`, `tasksNew` keys
- Section/group headers → add `tasksSection{Name}` or reuse `tab*` keys
- Always pass `t` to sub-components that render user text
